; B = 
<quantity id="5B3B9B30FFE4F82C114BF849FAB28197" box="[1301,1382,1982,2006]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
; C–F = 
<quantity id="5B3B9B30FFE4F82C14F2F816FEDD81BB" box="[172,265,2017,2042]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
; G–J = 
<quantity id="5B3B9B30FFE4F82C1509F815FE6181BB" box="[343,437,2018,2042]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" unit="mm" value="0.02">0.02 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C7C36D5FFE5F82A14C9F86EFCC38394" blockId="11.[151,1333,1945,1970]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1436,1434,1495]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="313" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">
<emphasis id="AEB7EAC7FFE5F82D14C9F86EFF3081F0" bold="true" box="[151,228,1945,1970]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">FIG. 7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="5BC34D56FFE5F82D14B4F86DFDE781F3" authority="Humes" authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1987" box="[234,563,1946,1970]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Aphotopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limatulus">
<emphasis id="AEB7EAC7FFE5F82D14B4F86DFE3681F0" box="[234,482,1946,1970]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">Aphotopontius limatulus</emphasis>
Humes
</taxonomicName>
, female. A, leg 1; B, leg 2; C, leg 3; D, leg 4; E, leg 5. Scale bars: 
<quantity id="5B3B9B30FFE5F82D108AF86EFAE581F3" box="[1236,1329,1945,1970]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="AEB7EAC7FFE2F82A14C9FA6DFF3783F1" bold="true" box="[151,227,1434,1459]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">FIG. 8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="5BC34D56FFE2F82A14B4FA6CFDE683F0" authority="Humes" authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1987" box="[234,562,1435,1459]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Aphotopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limatulus">
<emphasis id="AEB7EAC7FFE2F82A14B4FA6CFE3583F1" box="[234,481,1435,1459]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Aphotopontius limatulus</emphasis>
Humes
</taxonomicName>
, male. A, habitus, dorsal; B, anal somite and caudal rami, ventral; C, antennule; D, left legs 5 and 6, ventral. Scale bars: A = 
<quantity id="5B3B9B30FFE2F82A164EFA48FDB58394" box="[528,609,1471,1495]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
; B–D = 
<quantity id="5B3B9B30FFE2F82A16EBFA49FCC78394" box="[693,787,1470,1495]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C7C36D5FFE2F82A14C9F9F2FE2980C9" blockId="12.[151,1436,1541,2036]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Fifth pedigerous somite 102 μm wide. Genital somite 76 × 113 μm, much wider than long, with spinules on ventral surface of genital operculum (Fig. 8D). Four abdominal somites 46 × 73, 34 × 68, 24 × 64, and 40 × 60 μm, respec- tively. Caudal ramus (Fig. 8B) 146 × 20 μm, 7.30 times as long as wide. Anal somite and caudal rami with spinules on ventral surface, as in female.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C7C36D5FFE2F82A1499F961FEF28159" blockId="12.[151,1436,1541,2036]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Rostrum as in female. Antennule (Fig. 8C) 11-segmented; armature formula 1, 14, 8, 3, 2, 4, 2, 2, 2, 2 + aesthetasc, and 11; fourth segment with outgrowth tipped by two spiniform elements and with one minute seta; proximal seta on penultimate segment minute, obscure; antepenultimate segment with additional spiniform process. Antenna as in female.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C7C36D5FFE2F82A1499F8D2FC10817D" blockId="12.[151,1436,1541,2036]" box="[199,964,1829,1856]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Mandible, maxillule, maxilla, maxilliped, and legs 1–4 as in female.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C7C36D5FFE2F82A1499F8BDFE5981E9" blockId="12.[151,1436,1541,2036]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Leg 5 (Fig. 8D) 2-segmented; protopod short unarticulated from somite, with one large outer seta; exopod 27 × 21 μm, with three long outer setae and two inner knife-like setae. Leg 6 (Fig. 8D) represented by two long setae on genital operculum.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D4D9655EFFE2F82B1499F842FDF984C5" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="314" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9C7C36D5FFE2F82B1499F842FE6087C9" blockId="12.[151,1436,1541,2036]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1437,153,539]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="314" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis id="AEB7EAC7FFE2F82A1499F842FEEF818D" bold="true" box="[199,315,1973,1999]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="5BC34D56FFE2F82A151DF842FD27818D" authority="Humes, 1987" authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1987" box="[323,755,1973,2000]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Aphotopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limatulus">
<emphasis id="AEB7EAC7FFE2F82A151DF842FD81818D" box="[323,597,1973,1999]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Aphotopontius limatulus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F8524B24FFE2F82A1603F841FD27818D" author="Humes, A. G." box="[605,755,1973,2000]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" pagination="645 - 788" refId="ref16279" refString="Humes, A. G. (1987) Copepoda from deep-sea hydrothermal vents. Bulletin of Marine Science, 41, 645 - 788." type="journal article" year="1987">Humes, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has previously been reported from the East Pacific Rise and Galapagos Rift in the Pacific Ocean (
<bibRefCitation id="F8524B24FFE2F82A1619F82EFD0A81B1" author="Humes, A. G." box="[583,734,2009,2035]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" pagination="51 - 62" refId="ref16482" refString="Humes, A. G. (1998). Copepoda from deep-sea hydrothermal sites and cold seeps: description of a new species of Aphotopontius from the East Pacific Rise and general distribution. Cahiers de Biologie Marine, 39, 51 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.21411 / CBM. A. 958 AE 7 F 7" type="journal article" year="1998">Humes 1998</bibRefCitation>
). Our material from the Central Indian Ridge does not differ significantly from the 
<typeStatus id="43788877FFE3F82B15CBFF6EFE1186F1" box="[405,453,153,179]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">type</typeStatus>
specimens. The only notable differences were in the caudal ramus and antennule. The length-to-width ratio of the caudal ramus of the 
<typeStatus id="43788877FFE3F82B16F9FF4AFD038695" box="[679,727,189,215]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">type</typeStatus>
specimens was described 
<quantity id="5B3B9B30FFE3F82B17A7FF4AFB928695" box="[1017,1094,189,215]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5247599999999997" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" unit="in" value="9.94">9.94 in</quantity>
the female and 
<quantity id="5B3B9B30FFE3F82B10ADFF4AFAE58695" box="[1267,1329,189,215]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1843999999999997" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" unit="in" value="8.6">8.6 in</quantity>
the male, while it is 8.85 and 
<quantity id="5B3B9B30FFE3F82B152CFF16FE1486B9" box="[370,448,225,251]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8541999999999998" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" unit="in" value="7.3">7.30 in</quantity>
our female and male specimens, respectively. The two ventral patches of spinules on the mid-region of the caudal ramus are not mentioned in the original description. The antennule of the 
<typeStatus id="43788877FFE3F82B1087FEF2FADD875D" box="[1241,1289,261,287]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">type</typeStatus>
specimens is described as 10-segmented in the female and 12-segmented in the male, whereas it is 11-segmented in both sexes of our specimens. We consider these differences to be within species variation or artificial and insufficient to separate them as different species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C7C36D5FFE3F82B1490FE62FCC18459" blockId="13.[151,1437,153,539]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">
Four species in the 
<taxonomicName id="5BC34D56FFE3F82B15FBFE62FDF887ED" authorityName="Humes and Dojiri" authorityYear="1980" box="[421,556,405,431]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dirivultidae</taxonomicName>
have been recorded as transoceanic, from both the Atlantic and Pacific oceans: 
<taxonomicName id="5BC34D56FFE3F82B14C9FE4EFD848791" authority="Humes, 1987" authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1987" box="[151,592,441,467]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Aphotopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forcipatus">
<emphasis id="AEB7EAC7FFE3F82B14C9FE4EFE668791" box="[151,434,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Aphotopontius forcipatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F8524B24FFE3F82B15E6FE4EFD848791" author="Humes, A. G." box="[440,592,441,467]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" pagination="645 - 788" refId="ref16279" refString="Humes, A. G. (1987) Copepoda from deep-sea hydrothermal vents. Bulletin of Marine Science, 41, 645 - 788." type="journal article" year="1987">Humes, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5BC34D56FFE3F82B1604FE4EFC0C8791" authority="Humes, 1996" authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1996" box="[602,984,441,467]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirus">
<emphasis id="AEB7EAC7FFE3F82B1604FE4EFCED8791" box="[602,825,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Stygiopontius mirus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F8524B24FFE3F82B171EFE4EFC0C8791" author="Humes, A. G." box="[832,984,441,467]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" pagination="609 - 653" refId="ref16443" refString="Humes, A. G. (1996) Deep-sea Copepoda (Siphonostomatoida) from hydrothermal sites on the Mid-Atlantic Ridge at 23 ° and 37 °. Bulletin of Marine Science, 58, 609 - 653." type="journal article" year="1996">Humes, 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5BC34D56FFE3F82B17BCFE4EFADB8791" authority="Humes, 1987" authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1987" box="[994,1295,441,467]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinatus">
<emphasis id="AEB7EAC7FFE3F82B17BCFE4EFC248791" box="[994,1008,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="AEB7EAC7FFE3F82B17A0FE4DFBA58791" box="[1022,1137,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">pectinatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F8524B24FFE3F82B1029FE4EFADB8791" author="Humes, A. G." box="[1143,1295,441,467]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" pagination="645 - 788" refId="ref16279" refString="Humes, A. G. (1987) Copepoda from deep-sea hydrothermal vents. Bulletin of Marine Science, 41, 645 - 788." type="journal article" year="1987">Humes, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="5BC34D56FFE3F82B1117FE4EFEA187B5" authority="Humes, 1997" authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1997" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rimivagus">
<emphasis id="AEB7EAC7FFE3F82B1117FE4EFA838791" box="[1353,1367,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="AEB7EAC7FFE3F82B113AFE4DFF0C87B5" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">rimivagus</emphasis>
Humes, 1997
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F8524B24FFE3F82B15DAFE2AFDC387B5" author="Humes, A. G." box="[388,535,477,503]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" pagination="289 - 304" refId="ref16388" refString="Humes, A. G. (1990) Copepods (Siphonostomatoida) from a deep-sea hydrothermal vent at the Mariana Back-Arc Basin in the Pacific, including a new genus and species. Journal of Natural History, 24, 289 - 304. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222939000770211" type="journal article" year="1990">Humes 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F8524B24FFE3F82B167CFE2AFD8987B5" author="Humes, A. G." box="[546,605,477,503]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" pagination="609 - 653" refId="ref16443" refString="Humes, A. G. (1996) Deep-sea Copepoda (Siphonostomatoida) from hydrothermal sites on the Mid-Atlantic Ridge at 23 ° and 37 °. Bulletin of Marine Science, 58, 609 - 653." type="journal article" year="1996">1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F8524B24FFE3F82B1636FE2AFD7787B5" author="Humes, A. G." box="[616,675,477,503]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" pagination="51 - 62" refId="ref16482" refString="Humes, A. G. (1998). Copepoda from deep-sea hydrothermal sites and cold seeps: description of a new species of Aphotopontius from the East Pacific Rise and general distribution. Cahiers de Biologie Marine, 39, 51 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.21411 / CBM. A. 958 AE 7 F 7" type="journal article" year="1998">1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F8524B24FFE3F82B16F1FE2AFC5C87B5" author="Gollner, S. &amp; Ivanenko, V. N. &amp; Arbizu, P. M. &amp; Bright, M." box="[687,904,477,503]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" pagination="9801" refId="ref16060" refString="Gollner, S., Ivanenko, V. N., Arbizu, P. M. &amp; Bright, M. (2010) Advances in taxonomy, ecology, and biogeography of Dirivultidae (Copepoda) associated with chemosynthetic environments in the deep sea. PLoS ONE, 5, e 9801. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0009801" type="journal article" year="2010">
Gollner 
<emphasis id="AEB7EAC7FFE3F82B1752FE29FCE987B5" box="[780,829,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
). Here, 
<taxonomicName id="5BC34D56FFE3F82B1781FE2AFBB387B5" authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1987" box="[991,1127,477,503]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Aphotopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limatulus">
<emphasis id="AEB7EAC7FFE3F82B1781FE2AFBB387B5" box="[991,1127,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">A. limatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is reported as an additional transoceanic species from the Pacific and Indian Oceans.
</paragraph>
